<h1>Introduction</h1>

<p>The Throw Barbarian is a heavily gear dependent character that takes advantage of the @@@D2DoubleThrow@@@ and @@@D2ThrowingMastery@@@ Skills. While he can put out a lot of single target Damage, his AOE is very lacking so make sure to be careful in large groups or use @@@D2Howl@@@ to isolate Unique Minions. Although playthrough Damage without gear may take some time, eventually this Character is capable of taking on Uber Tristram if built correctly!</p>

<h1>Quick Reference</h1>

<h2>Skill Build</h2>

<p>The following section shows the core skills for the Throw Barbarian. For a detailed breakdown of all core and optional skills as well as the recommended order for allocating skill points, refer to the Skills section of this guide.</p>

<ol>
<li>1 point to all prerequisites</li>
<li>20 points to @@@D2DoubleThrow@@@ - Main Damage Skill, required</li>
<li>20 points to @@@D2DoubleSwing@@@ - Damage Synergy for @@@D2DoubleThrow@@@, required</li>
<li>1 points to @@@D2Leap@@@ - Helpful for avoiding Minions and movement, required</li>
<li>20 points to @@@D2ThrowingMastery@@@ - Main Damage Mastery, required</li>
<li>1 points to @@@D2IncreasedSpeed@@@ - Increases Barbarian movement, required</li>
<li>1 points to @@@D2NaturalResistance@@@ - Increases Resistances greatly, required</li>
<li>20 points to @@@D2BattleOrders@@@ - Massive Life and Mana gain, required</li>
<li>1+ points to @@@D2Howl@@@ - Useful for shouting Monsters away to isolate Uniques, required</li>
<li>1 points to @@@D2BattleCommand@@@ - Adds one more skill, required</li>
</ol>

